<paragraph id="8B9036ACFFBDFFF56DC8FB48FD9DFB1A" blockId="7.[151,519,1229,1255]" box="[151,519,1229,1255]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<heading id="D0D881C0FFBDFFF56DC8FB48FD9DFB1A" bold="true" box="[151,519,1229,1255]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B95BEABEFFBDFFF56DC8FB48FD9DFB1A" bold="true" box="[151,519,1229,1255]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D2FFFBDFFF56C10FB48FD9DFB1A" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1873" box="[335,519,1229,1255]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Blepharoneura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95BEABEFFBDFFF56C10FB48FD9DFB1A" bold="true" box="[335,519,1229,1255]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Blepharoneura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9036ACFFBDFFF56DC8FA92FF73FAAA" blockId="7.[151,1436,1303,1992]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Body nonmetallic, usually predominantly yellow, often with brown markings, occasionally predominantly brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9036ACFFBDFFF56D9AFAE1FBD4F9E4" blockId="7.[151,1436,1303,1992]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Head: Frons setulose, with 2 orbital setae and usually 2 frontal setae. Ocellar and postocellar setae well developed. Frontal vitta usually orange, red or brown with narrow yellow area medially (
<figureCitation id="13142A29FFBDFFF569F7FA0FFB77FA59" box="[1192,1261,1418,1444]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="8.[151,255,1130,1154]" captionTargetBox="[161,1424,214,1094]" captionTargetId="figure-75@8.[151,1436,194,1106]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 1. Habitus, dorsal: B. nigrifemur (Bolivia: Apa Apa, USNMENT00055924)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5315907" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5315907/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Facial carina weak. Vibrissa absent. Antenna moderately long but usually not reaching ventral margin of face. Arista long pubescent to short plumose. Prementum elongate and strongly convex. Labella with sclerotized ridges or spicules (modified pseudotracheal ring tips; often not exposed in dry specimens).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9036ACFFBDFFF56D9AF9A0FC0FF8FC" blockId="7.[151,1436,1303,1992]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Thorax: Yellow to orange, often with brown markings, particularly on mesonotum, in a few species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D2FFFBDFFF56DC8F9C9FE94F998" authorityName="Wulp" authorityYear="1899" box="[151,270,1612,1637]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Blepharoneura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="femoralis">
<emphasis id="B95BEABEFFBDFFF56DC8F9C9FE94F998" box="[151,270,1612,1637]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">femoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group predominantly brown (
<figureCitation id="13142A29FFBDFFF56FD3F9C9FCADF99B" box="[652,823,1612,1638]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 90–93" captionStart-1="FIGURES 94–97" captionStart-2="FIGURES 98–101" captionStart-3="FIGURES 102–105" captionStart-4="FIGURES 106–108" captionStartId-0="31.[151,274,1876,1900]" captionStartId-1="32.[151,269,1938,1962]" captionStartId-2="33.[151,279,1927,1951]" captionStartId-3="34.[151,281,1922,1946]" captionStartId-4="35.[151,271,1266,1290]" captionTargetBox-0="[184,1407,204,1826]" captionTargetBox-1="[163,1428,202,1904]" captionTargetBox-2="[158,1414,197,1893]" captionTargetBox-3="[161,1428,204,1866]" captionTargetBox-4="[152,1422,213,1207]" captionTargetId-0="figure-41@31.[164,1424,194,1852]" captionTargetId-1="figure-111@32.[151,1436,194,1914]" captionTargetId-2="figure-37@33.[155,1432,194,1903]" captionTargetId-3="figure-46@34.[151,1436,194,1898]" captionTargetId-4="figure-257@35.[151,1436,194,1242]" captionTargetPageId-0="31" captionTargetPageId-1="32" captionTargetPageId-2="33" captionTargetPageId-3="34" captionTargetPageId-4="35" captionText-0="FIGURES 90–93. Thorax, dorsal: 90–91, B. furcifer (Venezuela: Capirito, USNMENT00213927; Peru: Avispas, USNMENT00053665); 92, B. hirsuta (Brazil: Rio de Janeiro, USNMENT00054199); 93, B. septemdigitata (Peru: Erika, USNMENT00054208)." captionText-1="FIGURES 94–97. Thorax, dorsal: 94, B. thetis (holotype); 95, B. bivittata (Costa Rica: S Upala, USNMENT00054202); 96–97, B. brevivittata (Costa Rica: Rincon de Osa, USNMENT00054203; Costa Rica: Golfo Dulce, USNMENT00048518)." captionText-2="FIGURES 98–101. Thorax, dorsal: 98–99, B. quadristriata (Mexico: Los Tuxtlas, USNMENT00054200, USNMENT00054201); 100–101, B. femoralis (Mexico: El Triunfo, USNMENT00054206; San Cristobal, USNMENT00054205)." captionText-3="FIGURES 102–105. Thorax, dorsal: 102–104, B. marshalli (holotype; Argentina: Camino la Cornisa, USNMENT00054210, USNMENT00054211); 105, B. tau (holotype)." captionText-4="FIGURES 106–108. Thorax, lateral: 106, B. femoralis (Mexico: El Triunfo, USNMENT00213770); 107, B. apaapa (Bolivia: Apa Apa, USNMENT00055944); 108, B. chaconi (Costa Rica: San Gerardo, USNMENT00048386)." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5315939" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5361579" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5361581" figureDoi-3="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5361583" figureDoi-4="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5361585" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5315939/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5361579/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/5361581/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/5361583/files/figure.png" httpUri-4="https://zenodo.org/record/5361585/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Figs. 90–108</figureCitation>
). Scutum posteriorly usually with pair of brown markings or single band or larger mark, often with 2–4 vittae, especially anteriorly. 1–2 postpronotal setae (second seta often varies intraspecifically), 2 notopleural, 1 presutural and 1 postsutural postalar, 1 intra-alar, 1 postalar, often 1 intra-postalar, 1 dorsocentral, 1 acrostichal, 3 scutellar, 3 anepisternal (1 on upper fourth just anterior to phragma), 1 anepimeral, and 1 katepisternal setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9036ACFFBDFFF56D9AF888FD39F835" blockId="7.[151,1436,1303,1992]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Wing: Vein Sc subapically anteriorly turned at 80–90° angle. Veins R 
<subScript id="17AB34E9FFBDFFF56944F898FBB9F8D6" attach="right" box="[1051,1059,1821,1835]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">1</subScript>
, R 
<subScript id="17AB34E9FFBDFFF56917F898FBF8F8D6" attach="right" box="[1096,1122,1821,1835]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">4+5</subScript>
, Cu 
<subScript id="17AB34E9FFBDFFF569C9F898FB04F8D6" attach="left" box="[1174,1182,1821,1835]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">1</subScript>
and base of vein Cu setulose dorsally. Crossvein r-m near or distal to midlength of cell dm (measured along vein M). Cell bcu with elongate posterodistal lobe. Pattern usually predominantly brown with hyaline spots and marginal incisions, sometimes on apical third with hyaline bands; cells dm and cu 
<subScript id="17AB34E9FFBDFFF56EEBF811FC26F85F" attach="left" box="[948,956,1940,1954]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">1</subScript>
