<emphasis id="B95BEABEFFB2FFFA6CEDF81CFDB8F84D" box="[434,546,1945,1968]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">B. apaapa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Bolivia: Apa Apa, USNMENT00055942); 3, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D2FFFB2FFFA697DF81CFB78F84D" authorityName="Norrbom &amp; Condon" authorityYear="2010" box="[1058,1250,1945,1968]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Blepharoneura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macwilliamsae">
<emphasis id="B95BEABEFFB2FFFA697DF81CFB78F84D" box="[1058,1250,1945,1968]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">B. macwilliamsae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Costa Rica: NE Canon Genesis, USNMENT00048612); 4, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D2FFFB2FFFA6FD7F839FD7DF82E" baseAuthorityName="Wulp" baseAuthorityYear="1899" box="[648,743,1980,2003]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Blepharoneura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rupta">
<emphasis id="B95BEABEFFB2FFFA6FD7F839FD7DF82E" box="[648,743,1980,2003]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">B. rupta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Costa Rica: SE Rio Naranjo, USNMENT00213532); 5, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D2FFFB2FFFA68DBF839FE9CF80B" authorityName="Norrbom &amp; Condon" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Blepharoneura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wasbaueri">
<emphasis id="B95BEABEFFB2FFFA68DBF839FE9CF80B" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">B. wasbaueri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(holotype). See Materials and Methods section for explanation of numbering system for hyaline markings.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B9036ACFFB3FFFB6D9AFF1DFBCDFF25" blockId="9.[151,1436,152,680]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Abdomen: Occasionally entirely yellow, but usually yellow with brown spots or reticulate pattern to predominantly brown with medial yellow vitta or row of spots (
<figureCitation id="13142A29FFB3FFFB6EDFFF3BFC48FF25" box="[896,978,190,216]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="8.[151,255,1130,1154]" captionTargetBox="[161,1424,214,1094]" captionTargetId="figure-75@8.[151,1436,194,1106]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 1. Habitus, dorsal: B. nigrifemur (Bolivia: Apa Apa, USNMENT00055924)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5315907" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5315907/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13142A29FFB3FFFB6EBFFF3BFBD0FF25" box="[992,1098,190,216]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 113–118" captionStart-1="FIGURES 119–125" captionStartId-0="38.[151,273,1761,1785]" captionStartId-1="39.[151,270,1814,1838]" captionTargetBox-0="[175,1410,454,1722]" captionTargetBox-1="[170,1416,202,1770]" captionTargetId-0="figure-108@38.[151,1436,432,1737]" captionTargetId-1="figure-55@39.[151,1436,194,1790]" captionTargetPageId-0="38" captionTargetPageId-1="39" captionText-0="FIGURES 113–118. Abdomen, dorsal: 113, B. femoralis (USNMENT00054204); 114–115, B. marshalli (Argentina: Camino la Cornisa, USNMENT00054210–11); 116–117, B. chaconi (InBio002151664; INBio002539948); 118, B. tau (holotype)." captionText-1="FIGURES 119–125. Abdomen, dorsal: 119–120, B. septemdigitata (Peru: Pakitza, USNMENT00213939–40); 121, B. cornelli (holotype); 122, B. furcifer (USNMENT00053665); 123, B. hirsuta (Brazil: Manaus, USNMENT00054198); 124, B. brevivittata (Costa Rica: Rincon de Osa, USNMENT00054203); 125, B. quadristriata (Mexico: Los Tuxtlas, USNMENT00054201)." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5361589" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5361591" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5361589/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5361591/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">113–125</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9036ACFFB3FFFB6D9AFF60FE5EFE1A" blockId="9.[151,1436,152,680]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Female terminalia: Oviscape tapering, subconical to funnel-shaped (short, subconical, brown in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D2FFFB3FFFB6872FF60FA06FF03" authorityName="Wulp" authorityYear="1899" box="[1325,1436,229,254]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Blepharoneura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="femoralis">
<emphasis id="B95BEABEFFB3FFFB6872FF60FA06FF03" box="[1325,1436,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">femoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group). Aculeus short, broad (especially in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D2FFFB3FFFB6FCFFE89FD65FED8" authorityName="Wulp" authorityYear="1899" box="[656,767,268,293]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Blepharoneura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="femoralis">
<emphasis id="B95BEABEFFB3FFFB6FCFFE89FD65FED8" box="[656,767,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">femoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group), and flat; in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D2FFFB3FFFB6EB8FE89FBCCFED8" authorityName="Wulp" authorityYear="1899" box="[999,1110,268,293]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Blepharoneura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="femoralis">
<emphasis id="B95BEABEFFB3FFFB6EB8FE89FBCCFED8" box="[999,1110,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">femoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group usually with acute or blunt scales on medial membrane (e.g., 
<figureCitation id="13142A29FFB3FFFB6F2DFEB7FCBBFEB1" box="[626,801,306,332]" captionStart="FIGURES 126–135" captionStartId="40.[151,272,1841,1865]" captionTargetBox="[201,1396,180,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-83@40.[186,1411,180,1824]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURES 126–135. Aculeus: 126, B. bivittata (holotype, USNMENT00213023); 127, B. brevivittata (Costa Rica: Golfo Dulce, USNMENT00048518); 128, B. cornelli (holotype, INBio001228576); 129, B. lutea (Costa Rica: Pitilla, INBio000424938); 130, B. macwilliamsae (Costa Rica: La Cangreja, USNMENT00048509); 131, B. bipunctata (Ecuador: Otonga USNMENT00213903); 132–133, B. apaapa (Bolivia: Apa Apa, USNMENT00055947, USNMENT00213943); 134, B. hyalinella (Bolivia: Apa Apa, USNMENT00055931); 135, B. nigriapex (Bolivia: Apa Apa, USNMENT00055930)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5361595" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5361595/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs. 126–135</figureCitation>
); tip in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D2FFFB3FFFB6E21FEB7FB8EFEB6" baseAuthorityName="Schiner" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[894,1044,306,331]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Blepharoneura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poecilosoma">
<emphasis id="B95BEABEFFB3FFFB6E21FEB7FB8EFEB6" box="[894,1044,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">poecilosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group triangular, with numerous distinct serrations, each associated with internal channel (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBE4B5DFFB3FFFB6E6AFEDCFBF2FE8E" author="Condon, M. A. &amp; Norrbom, A. L." box="[821,1128,345,371]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="279 - 304" refId="ref102323" refString="Condon, M. A. &amp; Norrbom, A. L. (1994) Three sympatric species of Blepharoneura (Diptera: Tephritidae) on a single species of host (Gurania spinulosa, Cucurbitaceae): new species and new taxonomic methods. Systematic Entomology, 19, 279 - 304." type="journal article" year="1994">Condon &amp; Norrbom 1994</bibRefCitation>
, figs. 14–16), in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D2FFFB3FFFB6872FEDCFA06FE8F" authorityName="Wulp" authorityYear="1899" box="[1325,1436,345,370]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Blepharoneura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="femoralis">
<emphasis id="B95BEABEFFB3FFFB6872FEDCFA06FE8F" box="[1325,1436,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">femoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group truncate to subtriangular, with step-like or digitiform lobes (
<figureCitation id="13142A29FFB3FFFB6EC3FE05FBD3FE67" box="[924,1097,384,410]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 126–135" captionStart-1="FIGURES 136–145" captionStart-2="FIGURES 146–155" captionStart-3="FIGURES 156–164" captionStart-4="FIGURES 165–172" captionStart-5="FIGURES 173–181" captionStart-6="FIGURES 182–187" captionStartId-0="40.[151,272,1841,1865]" captionStartId-1="41.[151,271,1866,1890]" captionStartId-2="42.[151,274,1884,1908]" captionStartId-3="43.[151,273,1774,1798]" captionStartId-4="44.[151,271,1877,1901]" captionStartId-5="45.[151,274,1824,1848]" captionStartId-6="46.[151,270,1374,1398]" captionTargetBox-0="[201,1396,180,1810]" captionTargetBox-1="[208,1387,194,1827]" captionTargetBox-2="[192,1409,194,1860]" captionTargetBox-3="[153,1432,204,1749]" captionTargetBox-4="[202,1389,194,1853]" captionTargetBox-5="[185,1415,195,1800]" captionTargetBox-6="[181,1432,194,1350]" captionTargetId-0="figure-83@40.[186,1411,180,1824]" captionTargetId-1="figure-69@41.[182,1407,194,1836]" captionTargetId-2="figure-65@42.[188,1413,194,1863]" captionTargetId-3="figure-140@43.[153,1433,194,1750]" captionTargetId-4="figure-69@44.[180,1408,194,1853]" captionTargetId-5="figure-67@45.[167,1420,194,1800]" captionTargetId-6="figure-195@46.[155,1432,194,1350]" captionTargetPageId-0="40" captionTargetPageId-1="41" captionTargetPageId-2="42" captionTargetPageId-3="43" captionTargetPageId-4="44" captionTargetPageId-5="45" captionTargetPageId-6="46" captionText-0="FIGURES 126–135. Aculeus: 126, B. bivittata (holotype, USNMENT00213023); 127, B. brevivittata (Costa Rica: Golfo Dulce, USNMENT00048518); 128, B. cornelli (holotype, INBio001228576); 129, B. lutea (Costa Rica: Pitilla, INBio000424938); 130, B. macwilliamsae (Costa Rica: La Cangreja, USNMENT00048509); 131, B. bipunctata (Ecuador: Otonga USNMENT00213903); 132–133, B. apaapa (Bolivia: Apa Apa, USNMENT00055947, USNMENT00213943); 134, B. hyalinella (Bolivia: Apa Apa, USNMENT00055931); 135, B. nigriapex (Bolivia: Apa Apa, USNMENT00055930)." captionText-1="FIGURES 136–145. Aculeus: 136, B. aspiculosa (Mexico: El Triunfo, USNMENT00213912); 137, B. cyclantherae (Mexico: Rt. 95, USNMENT00052304); 138–142, B. femoralis (Guatemala: Coban, USNMENT00213771; Brazil: Nova Teutonia, USNMENT00213760, USNMENT00052320, USNMENT00213761; Peru: Chanchamayo, USNMENT00213960); 143, B. nigrifemur (Bolivia: Apa Apa, USNMENT00055925); 144, B. sinepuncta (Costa Rica: Zurquí, USNMENT00050130); 145, B. zumbadoi (Costa Rica: San Gerardo, INBio002578264)." captionText-2="FIGURES 146–155. Aculeus: 146–148, B. mexicana (Mexico: S Chapingo, USNMENT00213805–06; holotype, USNMENT00213858); 149, B. chaconi (Costa Rica: San Gerardo, USNMENT00048388); 150–151, B. quetzali (holotype); 152, B. bidigitata (Brazil: Interlagos, USNMENT00213839); 153–154, B. hirsuta (Guyana: Moraballi Creek, USNMENT00213793; Brazil: Rio de Janeiro, USNMENT00054199); 155, B. wasbaueri (holotype)." captionText-3="FIGURES 156–164. Aculeus: 156, B. fernandezi (Brazil: Santarem, USNMENT00213888); 157–158, B. furcifer (Ecuador: Limoncocha, USNMENT00213928; lectotype); 159, B. lutea (Costa Rica: Golfito, USNMENT00213824); 160, B. quadristriata (Mexico: Los Tuxtlas, USNMENT00054200); 161, B. rupta (Mexico: Teapa, USNMENT00213796); 162, B. ruptafascia (holotype); 163, B. septemdigitata (Peru: Pakitza, USNMENT00213937); 164, B. unifasciata (holotype). ln = length, wd = width (of tip and gap)." captionText-4="FIGURES 165–172. Aculeus: 165, B. amplihyalina (holotype); 166, B. marshalli (holotype); 167, B. multipunctata (holotype); 168, B. mikenoltei (holotype); 169, B. mexicana (Mexico: Mexico City, USNMENT00213809); 170, B. regina (Mexico: Lagunas de Zempoala, USNMENT00213846); 171, B. variabilis (Mexico: El Triunfo, USNMENT00213899); 172, B. bidigitata (Brazil: Nova Teutonia, USNMENT00213907)." captionText-5="FIGURES 173–181. Aculeus: 173–174, B. biseriata (holotype; Mexico: Huipulco USNMENT00213950; medial membrane not shown in 158); 175, B. sp. nr. biseriata (Mexico: E El Palmito, USNMENT00213947); 176–180, B. femoralis (lectotype; Guatemala: Coban, USNMENT00213771; Brazil: Nova Teutonia, USNM00213761; Mexico: Rio Molinos, USNMENT00213778; Mexico: Mexico City, USNMENT00213773); 181, B. punctistigma (Mexico: Los Tuxtlas, USNMENT00213914)." captionText-6="FIGURES 182–187. Aculeus: 182–183, B. osmundsonae (Mexico: Valle de Bravo, USNMENT00213962; Mexico: El Yukon, USNMENT00213953); 184–187, B. splendida (Mexico: San Blas, USNMENT00213873; Salto de Eyipantla, USNMENT00213877; Guatemala: Pochuta, USNMENT00213874; Venezuela: Rancho Grande)." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5361595" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5361597" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5361601" figureDoi-3="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5315941" figureDoi-4="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5361603" figureDoi-5="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5361605" figureDoi-6="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5361607" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5361595/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5361597/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/5361601/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/5315941/files/figure.png" httpUri-4="https://zenodo.org/record/5361603/files/figure.png" httpUri-5="https://zenodo.org/record/5361605/files/figure.png" httpUri-6="https://zenodo.org/record/5361607/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs. 126–187</figureCitation>
). 3 spermathecae (
<figureCitation id="13142A29FFB3FFFB687FFE05FF5CFE3D" captionStart="FIGURES 188–195" captionStartId="47.[151,272,1584,1608]" captionTargetBox="[152,1430,272,1551]" captionTargetId="figure-195@47.[151,1436,271,1607]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIGURES 188–195. Spermathecae: 188–190, B. femoralis (Mexico: Lagunas de Zempoala, USNMENT00213772; Oaxaca, USNMENT00213778; Brazil: Nova Teutonia, USNMENT00052306); 191, B. regina (2) (Mexico: Lagunas de Zempoala, USNMENT00213846); 192, B. quadristriata (3) (Mexico: Los Tuxtlas, USNMENT00213949); 193, B. furcifer (3) (lectotype). Egg: 194, B. femoralis (Mexico: Mexico City, USNMENT00213773); 195, B. lutea (Costa Rica: Golfito, USNMENT00213824)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5361611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5361611/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs. 188– 193</figureCitation>
), subspherical or occasionally conical, usually with sclerotized neck and/or small to large basal apodeme, surface without denticles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9036ACFFB3FFFB6D9AFE71FC0EFD7F" blockId="9.[151,1436,152,680]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Male terminalia: Lateral surstylus relatively short (
<figureCitation id="13142A29FFB3FFFB6E7DFE71FC4AFDF3" box="[802,976,500,526]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 196–199" captionStart-1="FIGURES 200–203" captionStartId-0="48.[151,269,1876,1900]" captionStartId-1="49.[151,280,1567,1591]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1433,511,1812]" captionTargetBox-1="[163,1421,214,1521]" captionTargetId-0="figure-156@48.[151,1436,503,1852]" captionTargetId-1="figure-193@49.[151,1436,194,1543]" captionTargetPageId-0="48" captionTargetPageId-1="49" captionText-0="FIGURES 196–199. Epandrium and surstyli, lateral and posterior: 196–197, B. femoralis (Brazil: Nova Teutonia); 198– 199, B. thetis (holotype)." captionText-1="FIGURES 200–203. Epandrium and surstyli, posterior: 200, B. amplihyalina (Argentina: Horco Molle, USNM00213855); 201, B. mexicana (Mexico, USNM00213821); 202, B. quadristriata (Mexico, Los Tuxtlas, USNM00213850); 203, B. rupta (Belize, Stann Creek, USNM00213797)." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5361613" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5361615" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5361613/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5361615/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs. 196–203</figureCitation>
), with epandrium forming near oval in posterior view. Glans with single membranous, non-spiculose, basal lateral lobe; elongate, basal half slender and membranous, distal half strongly sclerotized, cylindrical (
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D2FFFB3FFFB6EC1FDC4FBA3FDA7" baseAuthorityName="Schiner" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[926,1081,577,602]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Blepharoneura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poecilosoma">
<emphasis id="B95BEABEFFB3FFFB6EC1FDC4FBA3FDA7" box="[926,1081,577,602]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">poecilosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group) or stout and bulbous (
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D2FFFB3FFFB6DFEFDEDFE8AFD7C" authorityName="Wulp" authorityYear="1899" box="[161,272,616,641]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Blepharoneura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="femoralis">
<emphasis id="B95BEABEFFB3FFFB6DFEFDEDFE8AFD7C" box="[161,272,616,641]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">femoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group). Proctiger sometimes weakly bilobed ventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9036ACFFB3FFFB6D9AFD0BFB87FD55" blockId="9.[151,1436,152,680]" box="[197,1053,654,680]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Egg (
<figureCitation id="13142A29FFB3FFFB6C5BFD0BFE28FD55" box="[260,434,654,680]" captionStart="FIGURES 188–195" captionStartId="47.[151,272,1584,1608]" captionTargetBox="[152,1430,272,1551]" captionTargetId="figure-195@47.[151,1436,271,1607]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIGURES 188–195. Spermathecae: 188–190, B. femoralis (Mexico: Lagunas de Zempoala, USNMENT00213772; Oaxaca, USNMENT00213778; Brazil: Nova Teutonia, USNMENT00052306); 191, B. regina (2) (Mexico: Lagunas de Zempoala, USNMENT00213846); 192, B. quadristriata (3) (Mexico: Los Tuxtlas, USNMENT00213949); 193, B. furcifer (3) (lectotype). Egg: 194, B. femoralis (Mexico: Mexico City, USNMENT00213773); 195, B. lutea (Costa Rica: Golfito, USNMENT00213824)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5361611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5361611/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs. 194–195</figureCitation>
): Cylindrical ovoid, slightly curved, slightly tapered.
</paragraph>
